{"id":559,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":93,"title":"Cam15 - Test 4 - Part 1","subtitle":"Train Journey Satisfaction Survey","level":"B1","parts":94,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam15-test-4-part-1.559/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/0-ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Hello. Do you mind if I ask you some questions about your journey today?\nWe're doing a customer satisfaction survey.\nYes. OK. I've got about ten minutes before my train home leaves.\nI'm on a day trip.\nGreat. Thank you.\nSo first of all, could you tell me your name?\nIt's Sophie Bird.\nThank you.\nAnd would you mind telling me what you do?\nI'm a journalist.\nOh really? That must be interesting.\nYes. It is.\nSo was the reason for your visit here today work?\nActually, it's my day off.\nI came here to do some shopping.\nOh right.\nBut I do sometimes come here for work.\nOK.\nNow I'd like to ask some questions about your journey today, if that's OK.\nYes. No problem.\nRight, so can you tell me which station you're travelling back to?\nStaunfirth, where I live.\nAh, can I just check the spelling?\nSTAUNFIRTH?\nThat's right.\nAnd you travelled from there this morning?\nYes.\nOK, good.\nNext, can I ask what kind of ticket you bought?\nI assume it wasn't a season ticket, as you don't travel every day.\nThat's right. No, I just got a normal return ticket.\nI don't have a rail card so I didn't get any discount.\nI keep meaning to get one because it's a lot cheaper.\nYes - you'd have saved 20% on your ticket today.\nSo you paid the full price for your ticket?\nI paid £23.70.\nOK.\nDo you think that's good value for money?\nNot really.\nI think it's too much for a journey that only takes 45 minutes.\nYes, that's one of the main complaints we get.\nSo, you didn't buy your ticket in advance?\nNo.\nI know it's cheaper if you buy a week in advance but I didn't know I was coming then.\nI know.\nYou can't always plan ahead, so...\ner.. did you buy it this morning?\nNo, it was yesterday.\nRight.\nAnd do you usually buy your tickets at the station?\nWell, I do usually but the ticket office closes early and I hate using ticket machines.\nI think ticket offices should be open for longer hours.\nThere's always a queue for the machines and they're often out of order.\nHmm... A lot of customers are saying the same thing.\nSo to answer your question... I got an e-ticket online.\nOK.\nThank you.\nNow I'd like to ask you about your satisfaction with your journey.\nSo what would you say you were most satisfied with today?\nWell, I like the wifi on the train.\nIt's improved a lot.\nIt makes it easier for me to work if I want to.\nThat's the first time today anyone's mentioned that.\nIt's good to get some positive feedback on that.\nAnd, um... is there anything you weren't satisfied with?\nWell, normally, the trains run on time and are pretty reliable\nbut today there was a delay;\nthe train was about 15 minutes behind schedule.\nOK. I'll put that down.\nNow I'd also like to ask about the facilities at this station.\nYou've probably noticed that the whole station's been upgraded.\nWhat are you most satisfied with?\nOh... I think the best thing is that they've improved the amount of information about train times etc. that's given to passengers -\nit's much clearer -\nbefore there was only one board and I couldn't always see it properly,\nwhich was frustrating.\nThat's good.\nAnd is there anything you're not satisfied with?\nLet's see...\nI think things have generally improved a lot.\nThe trains are much more modern and I like the new café.\nBut one thing is that there aren't enough places to sit down,\nespecially on the platforms.\nOK,\nso I'll put 'seating' down, shall I, as the thing you're least satisfied with?\nYes, OK.\nCan I ask your opinion about some of the other facilities?\nWe'd like feedback on whether people are satisfied, dissatisfied or neither satisfied nor dissatisfied.\nOK.\nWhat about the parking at the station?\nWell to be honest, I don't really have an opinion as I never use it.\nSo, neither satisfied nor dissatisfied for that then.\nYes, I suppose so...\nOK, and what about...","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:50:05","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Hello. Do you mind if I ask you some questions about your journey today?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/1.mp3","time_start":0.0,"time_end":4.43},{"position":2,"content":"We're doing a customer satisfaction survey.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/2.mp3","time_start":4.51,"time_end":7.16},{"position":3,"content":"Yes. OK. I've got about ten minutes before my train home leaves.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/3.mp3","time_start":7.45,"time_end":11.73},{"position":4,"content":"I'm on a day trip.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/4.mp3","time_start":11.73,"time_end":13.04},{"position":5,"content":"Great. Thank you.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/5.mp3","time_start":13.04,"time_end":14.6},{"position":6,"content":"So first of all, could you tell me your name?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/6.mp3","time_start":14.69,"time_end":17.51},{"position":7,"content":"It's Sophie Bird.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/7.mp3","time_start":17.59,"time_end":19.55},{"position":8,"content":"Thank you.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/8.mp3","time_start":19.65,"time_end":20.63},{"position":9,"content":"And would you mind telling me what you do?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/9.mp3","time_start":20.71,"time_end":23.25},{"position":10,"content":"I'm a journalist.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/10.mp3","time_start":23.37,"time_end":24.69},{"position":11,"content":"Oh really? That must be interesting.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/11.mp3","time_start":24.77,"time_end":27.03},{"position":12,"content":"Yes. It is.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/12.mp3","time_start":27.03,"time_end":28.32},{"position":13,"content":"So was the reason for your visit here today work?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/13.mp3","time_start":28.59,"time_end":32.16},{"position":14,"content":"Actually, it's my day off.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/14.mp3","time_start":32.33,"time_end":34.36},{"position":15,"content":"I came here to do some shopping.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/15.mp3","time_start":34.45,"time_end":36.19},{"position":16,"content":"Oh right.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-15-test-4-part-1-2023-01-19-23-41-09/16.mp3","time_start":36.19,"time_end":37.15},{"position":17,"content":"But I do sometimes come here for work.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.co